    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="422" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d422">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Lord Lyons</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 23, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Sir</hi>: A British subject has written to
                            ask me to inquire from you whether you will grant permits to British
                            subjects to load ships with cotton in the Savannah river below the
                            confederate obstructions. Will you be so kind as to tell me what answer
                            I should make ?</p>
                <p>Yours, faithfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LYONS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
